author: ERIC ANDREAS Special to the Courier
title: ‘Girls rule’ Gritzmaker still Guru to beat
text:
‘Girls rule’ Gritzmaker still Guru to beat By ERIC ANDREAS Special to the Courier winfieldcourier.com | 0 comments This week there are three burning questions that come to mind: First, will Winfield score again this season? Second, will the Michigan punter be “accidentally” fed to the crocodiles in his home country of Australia? Finally — what did the people in Hawaii do to all those sharks that made them go on a feeding frenzy? I knew their football team stunk but c’mon! It was a wacky week on the turf again as Winfield laid another goose egg in Augusta, Kansas State got run over by Oklahoma (literally) and most of the crowd actually stayed and watched KU’s game until the very end as the Jayhawks played their best game of the year to date! Also, Southwestern delighted a packed homecoming crowd as the Builders SHUT OUT their rivals, the Bethany Swedes, by 24-0!
